ygData.msgSnippet: There are ruins here and there or what I take to be ruins...  can t go in them that I can see and maybe they are someone else s home that I don t know about.
ygData.messageBody:
There are ruins here and there or what I take to be ruins... can't go
in them that I can see and maybe they are someone else's home that I
don't know about. Too many sand giants wandering around there to
investigate for long.

-----Original Message-----
From: Rodney Miller [mailto:RMiller@...]
Sent: Monday, May 24, 1999 1:52 PM
To: 'eqpaladin@onelist.com'
Subject: Re: [eqpaladin] New Subject-keeping group alive!--Your Server


From: Rodney Miller <RMiller@...>

I have been through North and South ro and have not seen any remnants of
the
elvish empire as far as I can tell.

Grod

-----Original Message-----
From: Saffy Lynn [mailto:saffy@...]
Sent: Monday, May 24, 1999 3:34 PM
To: 'eqpaladin@onelist.com'
Subject: Re: [eqpaladin] New Subject-keeping group alive!--Your Server


From: Saffy Lynn <saffy@...>

I'm on the Xegony server (High Elf Paladin, level 14). I have a question
that maybe you can help me with. I have been traveling through Antonica
lately, but have not yet been to Ro. Since the Eldarr Woods used to
occupy
that land before Solusek destroyed it, I am wondering if there are any
remnants of the Elvish Empire. any information would be appreciated.

thanks,
Eglath

"By G'Quon, I cannot remember the last time I was in a fight like that!
No
moral ambiguity. No ancient and overpowering Enemy. They were, as you
say,
the Bad Guys, and we were the Good Guys....and they made a very
satisfying
*thump* when they hit the ground!"
--G'Kar, A Late Delivery from Avalon
